write download.py, with an global variable N at top. 
the download will read tif.json and spawn N threads. for each thread i in N,

1) pick all tif whose index%N=i  
2) for each tif name(without extension), check whether the name is in result folder
3) repeat poll file count in tifs folder, sleep 10s if count > 40
4) for name not in result, download to tmp folder. retry on exception.
5) copy the tif to tifs folder
6) continue to next iteration


